---
// Newsletter signup card.
// After Nicole creates a MailerLite Embedded Form (Forms → Create → Embedded),
// replace the form + script block below with the HTML MailerLite generates.
// The form they give you is self-contained JavaScript — it handles subscribe
// directly to MailerLite's API without needing a server endpoint.
//
// Current state: placeholder UI that prompts reader to email directly.
// This is safe-to-ship; wire MailerLite form on next revision.
---

<div class="newsletter-card">
  <h3>Stay warm by the hearth</h3>
  <p>
    New cozy fantasy, occasional book recommendations, early looks at the next
    Crossroads Inn book. No spam, unsubscribe any time.
  </p>

  <p class="signup-note">
    Newsletter signup coming shortly.
    In the meantime, drop a line to
    <a href="mailto:hello@jasonkrebsbooks.com?subject=Newsletter%20signup&body=Please%20add%20me%20to%20the%20Crossroads%20Inn%20newsletter.">hello@jasonkrebsbooks.com</a>
    and you'll be added as soon as the list opens.
  </p>
</div>

<style>
  .newsletter-card {
    background: var(--bg-accent);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
  .newsletter-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .newsletter-card p {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .signup-note a {
    color: var(--warm);
  }
</style>
